replies.text:
@captainprototype187 
Yeah you need to check each cell individually, if there are cells bellow average voltage ( for example, if 10 battery show about 3.5v and few cells are near 0v) then these cell will disconnect the whole pack, as this is a safety feature and why BMS is used. If this is the scenario then you found the reason why this hoverboard were not being used. But if all battery's are at the same voltage, then the BMS is faulty and if the design allows it you can change it and use the hoverboard. 
Good luck and if you still need help feel free to ask
